PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1772067789
OL,3,CUK enjoys hottest day of the year
OL,4,Cbefore cloudy skies return, Met Office
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"This has enabled cloud to clear
OL,8,Facross many parts of England and
OL,9,FWales, and with the sun at this time
OL,10,Fof year beginning to gather a bit of
OL,11,Fstrength it has warmed the air that
OL,12,Fbit more.
OL,14,F"Today (Wednesday), some parts of
OL,15,FSouth East England could reach 17 to
OL,16,F18C."
OL,18,FMr Harris added: "Temperatures across
OL,19,Fmuch of the UK are expected to drop
OL,20,Ftomorrow (Thursday), relative to
OL,21,Ftoday, as winds become more westerly.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUxD@EO]zD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
